## Simple Voting System – UNIX Shell Script

Project Overview
This project is a simple, menu-driven voting system written in Bash shell scripting.
Users can vote for one of three candidates — Alice, Bob, or Carol.
Votes are stored in a text file so results remain saved even after the program exits.

This project demonstrates basic UNIX concepts such as:
File handling
Loops
Menu-driven programming
Case statements
User input handling

Features
✔ Cast vote for one of three candidates

✔ Results saved in votes.txt

✔ View live results anytime

✔ Admin-only vote reset option

✔ Simple & clean menu interface

✔ Beginner-friendly UNIX project

Files in This Project
voting_system.sh → Main shell script
votes.txt → Stores vote counts
README.md → Project documentation

How to Run the Project
1️⃣ Give execute permission
chmod +x voting_system.sh
2️⃣ Run the script
./voting_system.sh

Usage Menu
The script displays the following options:

1) Vote for Class Representative
2) View Results
3) Reset Votes (Admin)
4) Exit

Code Summary
Each time a user votes, the script:

Reads current values

Updates the chosen candidate’s count

Saves the new totals

Reset option requires admin password:
“ananya123”

